title: Belgium: Catalan officials seek support for independence referendum in Brussels
description:
High representatives of Catalonia, including its President Carles Puigdemont, took part in 'The Catalan Referendum' meeting, held in the European Parliament in Brussels, Tuesday. The conference marked the first official visit of the Catalan officials to the European institutions.

Together with Vice President Oriol Junqueras and Minister of Foreign Affairs Raul Romeva, Puidgemont defended Catalonia's right to hold an independence referendum.

Oriol Junqueras, Catalan Vice President (Spanish): "What we want is to vote. To vote and to decide with out votes what our future will be and to collaborate with our responsibilities to build a much better Europe and a much better international community."
